---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Cannabis Inventory Management | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Expert guide to cannabis inventory management for dispensary entrepreneurs in Maine. METRC integration, compliance, and best practices."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1586528116311-ad8dd3c8310d?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Maine Cannabis Inventory Management</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">METRC compliance and operational excellence for Maine dispensaries</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Inventory Checklist</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>System Required</strong></td><td>METRC (Marijuana Enforcement Tracking Reporting Compliance)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal Basis</strong></td><td>28-B M.R.S. §301, OCP Rule Chapter 1</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Tag Requirement</strong></td><td>RFID tags on all packages (cultivator-sourced)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Inventory Reporting</strong></td><td>Daily sales upload; monthly physical inventory</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Audit Trigger</strong></td><td>>1% variance = automatic OCP review</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Cost</strong></td><td>$50-200/month + $40/pack of 1,000 RFID tags</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why METRC Matters</h2>
      <p>METRC is Maine's mandatory seed-to-sale tracking system. Under <strong>28-B M.R.S. §301</strong> and <strong>OCP Rule Chapter 1</strong>, every gram of cannabis must be tracked from cultivation to consumer. This isn't optional—it's your license to operate.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Compliance = Profit Protection" type="success">
      A single inventory discrepancy can trigger an OCP investigation that shuts you down. But here's the secret: tight inventory control actually IMPROVES your bottom line by reducing shrinkage and waste.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>METRC Integration: The 5 Core Functions</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Function</th><th>Your Responsibility</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>1. Package Tracking</strong></td><td>Receive RFID-tagged products, scan into system</td><td>Per delivery</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>2. Inventory Transfer</strong></td><td>Document all internal movements</td><td>Real-time</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>3. Sales Recording</strong></td><td>Sync POS with METRC for each transaction</td><td>Per sale</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>4. Waste Documentation</strong></td><td>Log all damaged/expired product destruction</td><td>As needed</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>5. Reporting</strong></td><td>Generate monthly inventory reports</td><td>Monthly</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pro-Hack: The 1% Rule</h2>
      <p><strong>The critical threshold:</strong> Maine OCP flags any inventory variance exceeding 1% between METRC records and physical counts. At 1%+, you face automatic audit and potential license suspension.</p>
      <p><strong>Pro-Hack:</strong> Run weekly "mini-audits" on 10% of SKU locations. Catch issues BEFORE they compound to 1%.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Daily Operations Workflow</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Time</th><th>Action</th><th>METRC Entry</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>AM Opening</td><td>Review yesterday's sales, check par levels</td><td>Dashboard review</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Delivery Window</td><td>Receive shipment, scan all packages</td><td>"Incoming Transfer" </td></tr>
          <tr><td>Throughout Day</td><td>POS syncs with METRC automatically</td><td>Auto-upload</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Closing</td><td>Reconcile POS receipts with METRC</td><td>Daily report</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Physical count of 10% of SKUs</td><td>Variance report</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Common METRC Mistakes (and How to Avoid)</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Mistake</th><th>Consequence</th><th>Prevention</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Forgetting to scan returns</td><td>Inventory variance</td><td>Mandatory scan protocol</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Untagged products</td><td>Cannot sell</td><td>Verify tags on receipt</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Delaying data entry</td><td>Lost transactions</td><td>Real-time entry rule</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Ignoring "on hold" products</td><td>Compliance violation</td><td>Daily hold review</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Inventory Best Practices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Weekly physical counts</strong> — Don't wait for monthly required count</li>
        <li><strong>FIFO rotation</strong> — First-in, first-out prevents expired product</li>
        <li><strong>Par level monitoring</strong> — Reorder before shelves empty</li>
        <li><strong>Staff training</strong> — Every employee needs METRC certification</li>
        <li><strong>Backup documentation</strong> — Keep offline records of all transactions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cost Breakdown</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Item</th><th>Cost</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>METRC Software</td><td>$50-200/month</td><td>Based on volume</td></tr>
          <tr><td>RFID Tags</td><td>$40/1,000</td><td>Provided by cultivator</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Scanner Hardware</td><td>$500-2,000</td><td>Handheld + fixed</td></tr>
          <tr><td>POS Integration</td><td>$0-300/month</td><td>Depends on POS system</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Training</td><td>$500-1,500</td><td>Initial staff cert</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Required:</strong> METRC integration is mandatory under 28-B M.R.S. §301</li>
        <li><strong>⚠️ Critical:</strong> Stay under 1% variance or face audit</li>
        <li><strong>💡 Pro-Hack:</strong> Weekly mini-audits catch problems early</li>
        <li><strong>📊 Daily:</strong> Reconcile POS with METRC every single day</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OCP Rules Chapter 1</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.metrc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">METRC Official Site</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Verify current requirements with OCP.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>